xmlText.p: British PM Johnson lands back in London

LONDON, Sept 25 (Reuters) - British Prime Minister Boris Johnson landed in London on Wednesday, returning early from New York after the Supreme Court ruled his suspension of parliament was unlawful. (Reporting by Kylie MacLellan; writing by Guy Faulconbridge)
